# Day 8 — query the frontier_explorer for unexplored regions worth going to.
#
# The caller (task_coordinator) supplies its current map-frame robot pose so
# the explorer can score frontier candidates by Euclidean distance without
# having to do its own TF lookup. The robot pose's frame_id is expected to
# match the map frame the explorer is using internally — typically "map".
#
# On success, frontier_goals[i] is a sample-able PoseStamped (orientation
# is set to identity; the controller is free to pick its own approach yaw).
# scores[i] / info_gains[i] / distances[i] mirror frontier_goals[i] in the
# same order, sorted by score descending. An empty frontier_goals list is
# the legitimate "environment fully explored" signal — success stays True.
#
# On failure (no /map yet, malformed map, etc.) success is False and
# message carries a short diagnostic; the other arrays are empty.
geometry_msgs/PoseStamped robot_pose
---
bool success
string message
geometry_msgs/PoseStamped[] frontier_goals
float32[] scores
int32[] info_gains
float32[] distances
